You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application utilizing Java 21 Virtual Threads experiences severe latency spikes and thread starvation under heavy load. The application calls an external HTTP payment gateway inside a `synchronized` block:

java
public class PaymentService {
    private final HttpClient client = HttpClient.newHttpClient();

    public synchronized String processPayment(URI uri) {
        try {
            HttpRequest request = HttpRequest.newBuilder(uri).GET().build();
            return client.send(request, HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString()).body();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            throw new RuntimeException(e);
        }
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a developer attempted to run asynchronous database writes inside a Spring `@Service` bean using `CompletableFuture`. The application is throwing `LazyInitializationException` and database writes are silently failing to commit to the database:

java
@Service
public class UserService {
    @Autowired private UserRepository userRepository;

    @Transactional
    public CompletableFuture<User> createUserAsync(UserDto dto) {
        return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> {
            User user = new User(dto.getName());
            return userRepository.save(user);
        });
    }
}
